## Project Structure
backend/
├── app/
│   ├── main.py              # FastAPI app factory
│   ├── config.py            # Settings via pydantic-settings
│   ├── database.py          # Async SQLAlchemy engine + session
│   ├── routers/             # APIRouter modules (one per domain)
│   ├── services/            # Business logic, no DB access
│   ├── repositories/        # DB access only, no business logic
│   ├── models/              # SQLAlchemy ORM models
│   ├── schemas/             # Pydantic request/response models
│   ├── middleware/          # Auth, logging, rate limiting
│   └── dependencies/        # FastAPI Depends() functions
tests/
├── conftest.py              # Fixtures: async client, test DB
├── test_routers/            # Integration tests (hit actual endpoints)
└── test_services/           # Unit tests (mock repositories)

## Coding Rules
- Every endpoint MUST have a response_model declared
- Use async def everywhere — no sync functions that touch DB or I/O
- Repositories return domain objects, never SQLAlchemy row objects directly
- Services call only repositories, never SQLAlchemy directly
- Use structlog.get_logger() — never print(), never logging.info()
- All secrets via environment variables — never hardcode credentials
- Passwords are NEVER returned in any response, ever

## Testing Rules
- Write the test file FIRST, then the implementation
- Use pytest-asyncio with @pytest.mark.asyncio
- Use httpx.AsyncClient with app transport for integration tests
- Minimum coverage: 70% overall, 100% on auth endpoints
- Every test must be independent — no shared state between tests

## Error Handling
- Use HTTPException with explicit status codes
- 400: bad input  401: unauthenticated  403: unauthorized
- 404: not found  409: conflict  422: validation (Pydantic auto)
- 500: never expose internal error details to clients

## FastAPI Conventions
- Organize routers with prefix and tags
- Use Depends() for auth, DB sessions, and pagination
- Version all routes: /api/v1/